Vol / Page:  45
Edition:
Quote:  As a rule, to drive a mob of sheep for any distance, takes not less than four hands ... <i>Ibid.</i> 46 It needs incessant care to prevent stragglers breaking away from the head and sides of the mob, and the rear of the flock, made up of the weaker sheep, requires an equally constant lookout. The horses are led or ridden, as the ground allows; ... but in driving through unknown country, the halts are made very much where the explorers find themselves at sundown.
